<link>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=BAMC;ac30f7c3.1501</link>   <description> Dear Colleague,<br><br>A quick reminder that the *abstract submission deadline* and *early-bird<br>registration deadline* is *Saturday 7 February 2015* for the 4th Joint<br>Meeting of the /British Mathematical Colloquium/ (BMC) and the /British<br>Applied Mathematics Colloquium/ (BAMC), to be held at the University of<br>Cambridge from 30 March to 2 April 2015. Moreover, accommodation is<br>selling fast, and already all of the cheapest rooms have sold out. [...]   </description>   <dc:date>2015-01-27T12:32:30+00:00</dc:date>   <dc:creator>BMC-BAMC 2015 Secretary</dc:creator>   <dc:identifier>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=BAMC;ac30f7c3.1501</dc:identifier> </item>  <item rdf:about="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=BAMC;a5c6eae8.1412">   <title>BMC/BAMC 2015 Registration open </title>   <link>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=BAMC;a5c6eae8.1412</link>   <description> Dear Colleague,<br><br>We invite you and your colleagues to attend the 4th Joint Meeting of the<br>/British Mathematical Colloquium/ (BMC) and the /British Applied<br>Mathematics Colloquium/ (BAMC), to be held at the University of<br>Cambridge from 30 March to 2 April 2015. Joint meetings are the<br>quinquennial opportunity for all British Mathematicians to meet<br>together, so please would you circulate this invite widely in your<br>department. [...]   </description>   <dc:date>2014-12-04T19:50:28+00:00</dc:date>   <dc:creator>BMC-BAMC 2015 Secretary</dc:creator>   <dc:identifier>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=BAMC;a5c6eae8.1412</dc:identifier> </item>  <item rdf:about="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=BAMC;77879449.1409">   <title>BAMC & BMC: 30th March 2015 to 2nd April 2015 </title>   <link>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=BAMC;77879449.1409</link>   <description> We invite you to Cambridge for the 2015 combined British Mathematical<br>Colloquium (BMC) and British Applied Mathematics Colloquium (BAMC).<br>Joint BMC/BAMC meetings only take place every five years, and this<br>meeting, hosted by the University of Cambridge, will also include a<br>special set of sessions and plenaries in honour of the 150th anniversary<br>of the London Mathematical Society. Keynote speakers at the meeting<br>will include Robert Calderbank, Ingrid Daubechies, Jacques Dumais, Phil<br>Hall, Peter Kronheimer, Sylvia Serfaty, Wendelin Werner and Andrew<br>Wiles, and a public lecture is scheduled to be given jointly by Stephen<br>Hawking and Michael Green. [...]   </description>   <dc:date>2014-09-23T16:18:46+01:00</dc:date>   <dc:creator>BMC-BAMC 2015 Secretary</dc:creator>   <dc:identifier>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=BAMC;77879449.1409</dc:identifier> </item>   </rdf:RDF>
